### What this gives you

| Situation | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `control-plane-endpoint` is a bare IP | Check is skipped entirely |
| Hostname resolves (DNS or existing `/etc/hosts`) | Silent `✓` and continues |
| Hostname **does not** resolve — user answers **y** | Appends `<primary-cp-ip>  k8s-api.example.com` to `/etc/hosts` on that node only (idempotent), prints the cleanup command |
| Hostname **does not** resolve — user answers **n** | Hard error with the exact `echo '…' \| sudo tee -a /etc/hosts` one-liner to run manually before retrying |

The check runs independently on every node (primary CP → additional CPs → workers) so each node gets the entry regardless of join order. The `grep -qF` guard makes repeated `maglev play` runs idempotent.
